This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for person re-identification, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which are a popular tool in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of improving the robustness of person re-identification systems, which is a topic of interest in the computer security (cs.CR) community.
